property_address: Room in Seattle, Washington, United States
listing_description: Welcome to your tranquil retreat nestled in the prestigious Queen Anne neighborhood of Seattle. Situated in the lower unit of a charming triplex, this cozy private room offers a serene escape just a stone's throw from Downtown. Convenient access to public transportation ensures easy exploration of the city's attractions, from Downtown to the trendy Ballard neighborhood.The spaceYour private room is thoughtfully appointed with all the essentials for a comfortable stay, within an apartment shared with fellow travelers. Enjoy daily cleaning and restocking of the kitchen and bathrooms, ensuring a pristine environment for your comfort and convenience.Parking Note:Please note that street parking is limited in the area, with only four private parking spots available for rent on a first-come, first-served basis. Two are up close and covered for $20/each per night and two spots are halfway up the hill on the left-hand side for $15/each per night. To secure parking, please inquire before booking, as availability cannot be guaranteed.Guest accessFeel at home with access to the kitchen, dining area, and bathrooms, while laundry facilities are not included. For your convenience, we offer optional services such early/late check-ins, parking, and early/late luggage pick-up for a nominal fee. property_address: Entire home in Seattle, Washington, United States
listing_description: Explore our mid-century modern oasis located on a peaceful, tree-lined street close to the heart of Seattle. This distinctive property boasts AC—a rare find in Seattle homes—and is equipped with a premium workstation in a separate office ideal for remote work. Our home also offers easy public transportation access and is just a stroll away from Green Lake's dining, entertainment, and nightlife options.We celebrate diversity and welcome guests from all backgrounds.The spaceExperience comfort and style in my newly renovated 1480 sq. ft. home, designed for a relaxing city stay. The spacious living, dining, and kitchen area is perfect for socializing, featuring a gourmet kitchen with high-end appliances (except a microwave). Enjoy meals at the table for four and unwind in the bright living room with a 50" OLED HDTV.Relax in the bathroom with a full-size tub and shower, complete with a hairdryer, curling iron, and organic bath soaps. Sleep peacefully in the bedroom with a new Casper memory foam bed, hypoallergenic synthetic down pillows, and built-in closet. Stay connected and productive with our high-speed fiber internet and comfortable office space.Proudly maintained with attention to decor and cleanliness, I invite you to experience my home’s welcoming atmosphere firsthand!NOTE: Please note that while our property is listed as an ‘entire house,’ it includes a separate, self-contained basement unit and maintenance/laundry space for the property. We are fully committed to respecting our guests’ privacy and ensuring a peaceful stay. This arrangement has been a key part of maintaining the high-quality experience we’ve proudly offered for over eight years. We appreciate your understanding and are always available to address any questions or concerns you may have.One additional note: The fireplace in the living room is currently inoperable while the lining is being repaired; when the fireplace is operable, there is a $35 fireplace cleaning fee and a $25/day firewood charge (NOTE: You are more than welcome to bring your own firewood when its operable, but please make sure you are careful bringing it in!). ----------Regarding SERVICE ANIMALS: We are aware of the value service animals bring to people and of AirBnB's policy of allowing service animals without discrimination unless health and safety become an issue. My parent suffers from severe pet allergies; this is her primary living space when not hosting guests. As such, we can only welcome non-shedding/no-dander companions to our house as we need to guarantee their health.Guest accessDuring your stay, you'll have full access to the entire first floor, including the charming front garden and outdoor seating areas. Please note that the bottom floor is not accessible to guests.For your convenience and security, you will be provided with a unique front door code that will be activated specifically for your stay. Additionally, you'll find ample free street parking available right in front of the house for your use.Other things to noteYou are just a short walk to Green Lake, one of Seattle's most beloved parks. Its expanse of water and green space in the center of a dense urban neighborhood draws thousands of people daily from all over the city. The park is a natural preserve for hundreds of trees, plants, numerous birds, and waterfowl species. The 2.8-mile path around the lake provides a perfect recreational spot for runners and walkers. Many others use the athletic fields or visit the park for boating, picnics, and swimming.You are also within a 10-minute (or less) drive, Uber, light rail, or bus ride to Seattle's world-class attractions. Take a ride to the top of the Space Needle, browse the craft vendors of Pike Place Market, stroll the shoreline of Discovery Park, see who's playing at the KeyArena, and tour the unique Chihuly Garden and Glass Museum. Head into downtown Seattle at night to dine out at a gourmet restaurant or local cafe. You may even stumble upon a hidden dive bar!Business travelers will appreciate the home's proximity to the city's major tech campuses, including Amazon and Expedia. Outdoor enthusiasts can enjoy everything from hikes in the Olympic or Cascade mountain ranges to more local attractions like paddle boarding on Lake Washington or a picnic in Gas Works Park!---------Just to let you know, our property has two distinct homes. When I'm not traveling for work, I reside in the guesthouse, accompanied by my friendly black lab, Hawk. Sometimes, I'm away, and another Airbnb guest might be staying on the property during such instances. While each space is separate and private, you might cross paths with fellow guests. If you do, don't hesitate to offer a friendly 'hi!' as you enjoy the communal charm of our property.Please note that while our property is listed as an ‘entire house,’ it includes a separate, self-contained basement apartment and garage storage and maintenance area. The basement unit is infrequently occupied. When it is, it is typically only by our property manager and his young son when necessary. They are fully committed to respecting our guests’ privacy and ensuring a peaceful stay. This arrangement has been a key part of maintaining the high-quality experience we’ve proudly offered for over seven years. We appreciate your understanding and are always available to address any questions or concerns you may have.---------NOTE: We require that all guests staying at the property are accounted for in the booking details, primarily for safety and insurance purposes. All third-party bookings must be disclosed and approved prior to booking.Registration numberSTR-OPLI-19-001650
